frameDefinitions: An Entity is declared to exist, generally irrespective of its position or even the possibility of its position being specified.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
This frame concerns  words that express an Object's position on a scale, its Measurement, with respect to some attribute, its Dimension.
A Group is described as having members which are similar or dissimilar to each other.
A specified Designer or a Brand creates and distributes a Collection of related Products.
A salient Subevent has a Pattern of recurrence within a larger Process.
frameExamples: Finally, Poland ceased to <t>exist</t> as a state for hundreds of years.
An <t><fex name='Agg'>army</fex></t> of postal workers descended on my office.
The <t>diversity</t> of students here is to be applauded . INI
The new Gucci <t>line</t> is due out in early Spring.
Tony's fingers tapped <t>rhythmically</t> on the keyboard
listRoleDefinitions: Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist.
A time at which the entity is in existence.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Dimension</fen> which is measured.  Most LUs in this frame incorporate the <fen>Dimension</fen>.
<fen>Object</fen> identifies the item which is measured along one of its <fen>Dimension</fen>s.
<fen>Measurement</fen> identifies the extent of the <fen>Object</fen> along the specified <fen>Dimension</fen>.
This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose diversity is at issue.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the <fen>Group</fen> is assessed.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Group is diverse or homogenous.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the general area in which diversity occurs or exists.
The company that produces the <fen>Collection</fen> of <fen>Products</fen>.
The set of <fen>Products</fen> produced by the <fen>Brand</fen>.
The individual items produced by the <fen>Brand</fen>.
The larger event that is characterized by the recurring Subevents.
The salient, punctual event that is construed as part of a <fen>Process</fen>.
The <fen>Pattern</fen> that can be detected in the recurrence of  the <fen>Subevent</fen>s of the <fen>Process</fen> .

<fex>The  new vase</fex> is 5 cm in circumference at the top.

They're so damn rich, they could buy this whole <fex><t>line</t></fex> without batting an eyelash.
